guest_info.name: Fee Gentry
guest_info.title: CEO

main_topics: Impact of technology and AI on real estate

problems_addressed.specific_problem: Agents feeling overwhelmed by market changes and technology
problems_addressed.solution_summary: Focus on mindset, make a decision to thrive, and create a simple action plan.

problems_addressed.specific_problem: Agents leaving money on the table by not leveraging partnerships
problems_addressed.solution_summary: Identify and create strategic partnerships with vendors to earn additional revenue streams.

problems_addressed.specific_problem: Concerns about the future of real estate with AI and market changes
problems_addressed.solution_summary: Adapt by focusing on collaborative capitalism and building strong networks.

target_avatars.relevance: The episode provides insights on how to elevate business practices and increase revenue streams.

target_avatars.relevance: Offers strategies to rejuvenate their business model and adapt to industry changes.
target_avatars.key_takeaway: Shift from a transactional mindset to a business owner mindset by leveraging existing relationships.

episode_summary: Fee Gentry discusses how real estate agents can future-proof their businesses by focusing on mindset, creating strategic partnerships, and leveraging additional revenue streams. She emphasizes the importance of adapting to industry changes and building strong networks to thrive in a rapidly evolving market.
